x4freetext: A.V.F. Radial Ridge cyclotron
The targets were self-supported foils about 1 mg/cm2
thick, enriched isotopically up to 98.46% (64Zn),
Two detector telescopes with a fixed
angular separation of 5+ - 0.02 degr. were used. Each
telescope consisted of a dE-E pair of silicon
surface barrier detectors, typically 0.1 mm and 1.0 mm
thick, which were cooled to 0 degr. The energy
resolution was typically 200 keV FWHM. (Description
The differential cross section were normalized to the
prediction of the optical model for the elastic
scattering at low angles (<50 degr.).

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Error from the graphic bars. No source of
uncertainties is given.
For the first 2 + and 3 - states the statistical
accuracy was 6% or better for angles below 40 degr.,
3% or better for angles from 40 to 130 degr. and not
worse than 5% on maxima and 15% in deep minima for
angles larger than 130 degr., except for 70Zn, that
due to the presence of 64,66, 68Zn contamination,
accuracy for angles larger than 130 degr. was not
better than 15%. For all the other excited states,
the angular range measured goes from about 50 to
172.5 degr., being the statistical accuracy, in
general, not worse than 15% for angles below 130
degr. and not worse than 30% for angles larger than
130 degr., except for some deep minima.
Sub 002, 005, 008, 011 were deleted
(duplication of F0841). Data presentation was changed.
